OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Sat 18 Apr to Mon 27 AprFA
OL,6,Ffew showers around at the start of the
OL,7,Fperiod, mainly affecting the northwest
OL,8,Fwhere it will also be windy for a
OL,9,Ftime. For many though the weekend
OL,10,Fshould be fine and dry with spells of
OL,11,Fwarm sunshine, but still some chilly
OL,12,Fnights. Into the following week fronts
OL,13,Fassociated with another Atlantic low
OL,14,Fwill try to push into the UK, but may
OL,15,Fstruggle to make inroads against an
OL,16,Farea of high pressure to the
OL,17,Fnortheast. So the greater chance of
OL,18,Fsome rain is for western areas, while
OL,19,Fnorthern and eastern areas may well
OL,20,Fsee plenty of dry weather.
OL,21,FTemperatures likely remaining above
OL,22,Faverage.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
FL,164,160,301,260,100,100
